title.narrative: Senegal River Basin Multi-purpose Water Resources Development Project

description.narrative: The Program Development Objective is to enhance regional integration among the riparian countries of the Senegal River Basin through OMVS for multi-purpose water resources development to foster improved community livelihoods.The Project Phase 1 Development Objective is to improve management and use of water resources in the Senegal River Basin.

condition.narrative: Recip. shall take all necessary actions no later than 04/30 of each calendar yr. to make available to OMVS sufficient counterpartfu nds to cover Recip. financial contribution.
The PIE has hired an external auditor with qualifications, experience and TORs acceptable to the Assoc.
The PIE has updated its administrative and accounting manual and software.
The SA in form and substance satisfactory to the Assoc. has been duly executed on behalf of Recipient and PIE.
The conditions of effectiveness of Mauritania, Mali, and Guinea FA have beeen satisfied.
The conditions precedent to the effectiveness of the Guinea Membership Treaty dated March 17, 2006 have been satisfied.
The mgt contracts referred to in Sched. 2 para 3 to the PA have been duly executed by the parties thereto.
